history.content:
Just get midterms back and thinking about dropping your computer science class? Join the Society of Women Engineers for a talk and drop-in hours hosted by Edlyft. The Edlyft team will share their experiences getting over the steep computer science learning curve and landing great internships. Come from 12-1pm for a talk and after 1pm for 1:1 coffee chats. Plus free cookies! 🍪
 
Register for the event here:
https://forms.gle/6B9gJ9ohcmnagYUE9
FB Event: https://www.facebook.com/events/427012828094386/?active_tab=about
 
Disclaimer: This is NOT a content session for any classes, this session is designed for organizational and management skills specifically related to computer science classes.
history.subject: Computer Science Catch Up Session w/ SWE & Edlyft
